the complex reasoning behind interest rate adjustments. 
</P>
<P>
 Citing the oft-repeated "natural" rate of employment as dictating Fed action, 
Kuttner completely ignores relevant currency and monetary policy issues. The 
dollar's long-term slide against the yen and German mark, and the causal effect 
on the real value of U.S. debt and trade deficit are of crucial importance in 
