by 'on the other hand.' " 
</P>
<P>
 The divergence of opinion among economists is reason enough to examine the 
track record of those in charge. Greenspan wrote letters to the bank regulators 
asking them to exempt 14 savings and loans from the more Draconian regulatory 
provisions of the law due to their great expertise in dealing in sophisticated 
investments. Of those 14, only two are left in business. The remaining dozen, 
including Lincoln Savings, were turned over to the Resolution Trust Corp. He 
subsequently was appointed to his present position at the helm of the Fed. 
