<HEADLINE>
<P>
38-YEAR-OLD EASTSIDE MAN IS KILLED IN HIT-AND-RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's homicide detectives were investigating the hit-and-run death of a 
38-year-old Eastside man who was struck Thursday after being involved in an 
altercation with the car's driver.The incident may have been gang-related, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, whose name was being withheld pending notification of relatives, 
was hit in the 300 block of Dangler Avenue on the Eastside at 12:10 p.m., said 
Sheriff's Sgt. Ron Spear. The driver fled and the victim was taken to Los 
Angeles County-USC Medical Center, where he was declared dead an hour later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
