<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MAN ARRESTED ON MOLESTATION CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 27-year-old farm worker has been arrested on suspicion of molesting an 
8-year-old girl whom his wife was baby-sitting at their Oxnard home, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin Castro Suarez was taken into custody at his job in Somis on Wednesday 
morning, a year after police first obtained a warrant for his arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 Detective Ken Kent said Suarez agreed to be interviewed by Oxnard police in 
late 1993, then moved from his home to an unknown address. Officers picked him 
up this week after learning that he was working at a Somis farm. 
</P>
<P>
 Kent said the incident occurred when the 8-year-old girl and her younger 
brother were left at Suarez's home overnight. Because it was a cold night, 
Suarez's wife allowed the children to sleep in the couple's bed. Then in the 
morning, when she left to fix her husband a sandwich, Suarez allegedly molested 
the girl, Kent said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl later told her mother about the incident. The county Public Social 
Services Agency referred the complaint to Oxnard police for investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 Suarez was being held in County Jail late Thursday in lieu of $50,000. JULIE 
FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
