<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIQUOR STORE CLERK LIKELY TO SURVIVE BEING SHOT IN HEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Westminster liquor store clerk is expected to survive after being shot in 
the head by ayouth Wednesday night, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shawn Kim, 29, a clerk at TJ's Liquor, 15456 Brookhurst St., confronted three 
youths who appeared to be teen-agers as they were leaving the store without 
paying for beer, according to Sgt. Dan Kerr of the Westminster Police 
Department. One of the youths dropped the beer and shot the clerk with a 
pistol, Kerr said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim was rushed to UCI Medical Center, where he was listed in guarded condition 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The youths, who were still are large, fled northbound on Brookhurst in an 
older-model blue Nissan Sentra, police said. 
</P>
