<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL; VILLANOVA ADVANCES IN GREAT ALASKA SHOOTOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eric Eberz scored a career-high 23 points and No. 21 Villanova had runs of 
18-0 and 17-2 to defeat Alaska-Anchorage, 75-58, Thursday in the first round of 
the Great Alaska Shootout at Anchorage. 
</P>
<P>
 Eberz, a junior forward, scored 17 of Villanova's 33 second-half points.Jason 
Lawson added 17 points and Kerry Kittles added 12. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wildcats (1-0), bigger and quicker than Division II Alaska-Anchorage at 
every position, led, 44-37, early in the second half before going on a 17-2 run 
which included three-pointers by Roscoe Harris and Eberz. 
</P>
<P>
 The Seawolves (4-1) were led by Jason Kaiser, who scored 21, and Dana Pope 
with 20 points and eight rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The Seawolves led, 26-23, late in the first half before the Wildcats scored 18 
unanswered points over a four-minute span. 
</P>
<P>
 Villanova advanced to play the winner of Thursday's late game between No. 5 
Arizona and Minnesota. 
</P>
