<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; USC; IRISH'S GOHEEN OUT WITH INJURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Notre Dame linebacker Justin Goheen, once considered a candidate for the 
Butkus Award, is out of Saturday's USC game because of a shoulder injury, 
incurred two weekends ago against Florida State. 
</P>
<P>
 Guards Jeremy Akers (shoulder) and Mark Zataveski (neck) are out of Saturday's 
game.Defensive end Renaldo Wynn (turf toe) and cornerback Tracy Graham (neck) 
are listed as questionable. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame Coach Lou Holtz said cornerbacks LaRon Moore and Shawn Wooden were 
injured in Monday's practice and their status for USC was also questionable. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Irish senior running back Lee Becton, who scored on a 70-yard run on the 
second play of the game in Notre Dame's 31-13 victory over USC last year, ended 
that season with six consecutive 100-yard games.  
</P>
<P>
 But the 113 yards he had against Air Force last week was his first 100-yard 
game of this season. His off-year is attributed both to a stubborn groin injury 
and a constantly changing Notre Dame offensive line. If he gains 73 yards 
against the Trojans, he'll become Notre Dame's No. 10 career rusher. 
</P>
<P>
 Against USC last year at South Bend, he had 178 yards in 20 carries, his 
career high. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
