<TEXT>
<P>
 Mexico's Retail, Wholesale Sales Rise: Retail sales rose 11% in September over 
the same month last year, a government agency said. It was the largest increase 
in two years and the second consecutive monthly gain.Wholesale sales rose 4.4% 
in September, the fifth consecutive monthly rise. The figures are from a survey 
conducted by the government's Instituto Nacional de Estadistica Geografia e 
Informatica. It covered Mexico City, Guadalajara and Monterrey, the country's 
three largest cities. For the first nine months, retail sales rose 0.4% and 
wholesale sales 5.2% over the year-earlier period. The survey also reported 
that the number of people employed in retail commercial establishments in the 
three cities declined 1.8% in September and that the number of people hired in 
wholesale outlets fell 4.4%. Retail workers' real wages rose 1.4% in September. 
</P>
