<P>
 Namibia Gets 50% Stake in Diamond Industry: De Beers, the world's largest 
diamond producer, gave up its monopoly on diamond mining in the African country 
in exchange for a guaranteed stake in the industry for 25 years. Under an 
agreement signed by President Sam Nujoma and De Beers Chairman Julian Ogilvie 
Thompson, a new mining concern split 50-50 between the government and De Beers 
will take over all diamond mining. The agreement marks a compromise between the 
domination enjoyed by De Beers in Namibia since 1919. 
</P>
