<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY: BANK TO BUY BACK STOCK FOR GANIS CREDIT DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bank of Boston Corp. will buy back up to $50 million worth of its stock to 
make up for shares being issued for employee stock plans and the purchase of an 
Orange County finance company. 
</P>
<P>
 The bank said earlier this month that it plans to purchase Ganis Credit Corp. 
in Newport Beach for up to $36 million in stock. 
</P>
