<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAFT'S POLK SELECTED CONFERENCE MVP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Taft High's DaShon Polk, a senior safety/wide receiver, was named the most 
valuable player in the Northwest Valley Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Polk, 6-foot-3, 215 pounds, caught 28 passes for 442 yards and eight 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 He also intercepted two passes and earned a reputation as a ferocious hitter. 
</P>
<P>
 Polk also scored on an 88-yard run, a 92-yard kickoff return and completed 
five passes for 140 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
